subject: p13475033
Findings: Generalized chronic interstitial fibrosis and coarse interstitial markings compatible with interstitial lung disease is unchanged. There is no superimposed consolidation suggestive of pneumonia. There is no pleural effusion or pneumothorax. The cardiac and mediastinal silhouettes are stable. There is no free air beneath the right hemidiaphragm.
Impression: No superimposed pneumonia in a patient with known chronic interstitial lung disease.
